dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c O'Brien b Cusack 64 (74b 4x4 1x6 127m) SR: 86.48

dismissalComment.html: another one bites the dust. Younis tries to end it with a big hit and doesnt time it well and flies into Kevin's hands at mid-wicket

commentTextItems.html: Cusack pitched it too short and its allowed Akmal the chance to rock back and pull the ball to the square leg boundary. So Pakistan win the game by five wickets

commentPostTextItems.html: Pakistan have won an exciting game here in Belfast today by five wickets. It was a much more competitive game than the first ODI on saturday and both sides will be able to take positives from the game.

Ireland batted with much more consistency and Paul Stirling hit a very good century. The Irish will feel that they probably needed twenty more runs. Pakistan will be happy that they chased down the total without too much trouble.
The run rate never got out of control and there was good fifty's from both Younis Khan and Umar Akmal. Paul Stirling has been named man of the match for his excellent century.

So Pakistan complete a 2-0 series win over Ireland to continue the good run that they started on the tour in the West Indies. That just leaves me to thank you for following ESPNCricinfo's coverage of the two games. Its good evening from me, Justin Smyth here in Belfast.

dismissalText.commentary: Taufeeq Umar c Stirling b O'Brien 31 (43b 3x4 1x6 74m) SR: 72.09

dismissalComment.html: full delivery again from O'Brien and it pops up to Stirling at mid-wicket. Big Wicket for Ireland

dismissalText.commentary: Azhar Ali c Stirling b Rankin 39 (65b 4x4 0x6 83m) SR: 60

dismissalComment.html: and another one goes down for Pakistan. Rankin sent another fast delivery outside off stump, Azhar had to play at it. It took the edge and flew to Stirling at first slip

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq c †Wilson b Mooney 32 (53b 1x4 1x6 53m) SR: 60.37

dismissalComment.html: pitched outside off stump and looks to take the edge and Wilson takes the catch. Misbah stands his ground. He does look happy but the umpires given it. Its just what Ireland needed

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan c O'Brien b Cusack 64 (74b 4x4 1x6 127m) SR: 86.48

dismissalComment.html: another one bites the dust. Younis tries to end it with a big hit and doesnt time it well and flies into Kevin's hands at mid-wicket
